Uganda’s Police Arrest Opposition Leader after Protesting About Inflation

-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 
2011-05-05T11:58:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/uganda-s-police-arrest-opposition-leader-after-protesting-about-inflation.html
The leader of  Uganda ’s oppostion
 Democratic Party , Norbert Mao, was arrested today as he
attempted to walk to work in protest against rising inflation,
his party said.  Mao was arrested after he walked a short distance from his
home in Ntinda, a suburb of the capital, Kampala, Vincent
Mayanja, the party’s deputy secretary-general, said by phone.
Mao is detained at a police station in the city, he said.  Police deputy spokesman Vincent Ssekate didn’t answer his
phone when called today for comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
